). On the other hand, inspired by a\nmodified Angstrom method proposed by Zhu recently, we suggest a new data\nreduction methodology which takes advantage of the phase shift on both S1 and\nS2 as well as the amplitude on S1. Based on the simulation results, it is\nexpected that the non-ideality associated with the three observables may be at\nleast partially cancelled out.Therefore, the frequency window selection for\ncarrying out the data fitting is not sensitive to the magnitude of\n${\\alpha_{\\parallel ,C}}$. For typical specimen films whose in-plane thermal\nconductivity ranges from 0.84 W m-1 K-1 to 50 W m-1 K-1, the method proposed\nhere yields a theoretical measurement uncertainty of less than 5%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 19 Dec 2020 06:31:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-22"}
